  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (expanded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The operating envelope was extended post-validation to include paediatric patients (body surface area < 0.6 m²) and reduced flow rates (1.0–1.5 L/min) following a post-market clinical feedback cycle in Q4 2024. The assessment team judged that the original validation campaign, which covered adult flow rates of 2.0–6.0 L/min, provides sufficient coverage of the expanded range on the basis of dimensional similarity arguments and the monotonic behaviour of the hemolysis power-law model across Reynolds numbers. No additional experimental validation data covering the paediatric sub-population or the 1.0–1.5 L/min regime have been linked to this package.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
